Who is Joshua Smith? I am an interior designer, a certified life coach, and a certified meditation teacher. I combine all of this in my ethos when it comes to home and everyday living. You’ll hear lots from me about interior design but also about your “interior design” – meaning the inner world of body, mind, and spirit that you move through the external world with each and every day.⁠

What we do first thing in the morning sets the tone for our ENTIRE day, so set 15 minutes aside to complete the "3 Fives" Routine.⁠
⁠
Why the 3 Fives? This spiritual fitness routine is an easy way to open up a sacred experience with your Higher Self every morning before taking on the crazy and unpredictable times of our world. ⁠
⁠
Head over to our blog to learn more or drop your questions in the comments!

The start of the new year is a wonderful time to dive deeply into self-reflection. Here are some questions to ask yourself as you enter this new year: ⁠
▫️ In what moments did I feel the most like myself in 2022? ⁠
▫️ Where did I find the most peace in 2022? ⁠
▫️ What things from 2022 do I need to leave behind? ⁠
▫️ What wounds need to be healed from 2022? ⁠
▫️ What do I want to be true of my 2023? ⁠
▫️ Where can I bring light into life in 2023? ⁠
⁠
📸: @briannabroylesphoto
